Exploratory Data Analysis

## Important Variable Selection
## By Randomforest
library(randomForest)
## randomForest 4.6-10
## Type rfNews() to see new features/changes/bug fixes.
impvar <- randomForest(FREQ~., data = twolane, ntree=100, keep.forest=FALSE, importance=TRUE)
varImpPlot(impvar, main="Urban 2-lane")

impvar <- randomForest(FREQ~., data = fourlane, ntree=100, keep.forest=FALSE, importance=TRUE)
varImpPlot(impvar, main="Urban Muti-lane")

impvar <- randomForest(FREQ~., data = int, ntree=100, keep.forest=FALSE, importance=TRUE)
varImpPlot(impvar, main="Urban Interstates")

## Correlation plot
library(corrplot)
corrp <- cor(twolane)
corrplot(corrp, method = "circle")

corrp <- cor(fourlane)
corrplot(corrp, method = "circle")

corrp <- cor(int)
corrplot(corrp, method = "circle")

Data Modeling

### Generalized linear model (Poisson)[all data]
### Urban 2-lane
lmdel <- glm(FREQ~., data = twolane, family="poisson")
m <- predict(lmdel, type="response") ## FITTED VALUE
m1 <- fitted.values(lmdel)

vplayout <- function(x, y)
viewport(layout.pos.row = x, layout.pos.col = y)
